model_explanation: the focus in S1 is on BILL. This entails that Sam did not give bananas to anyone else. S2 says Sam gave Bill something else (grapes), which does not contradict that Sam only gave Bill bananas. It contradicts the typical reading of ‘only’ as it limits the kind of thing given; S2 contradicts the intended meaning that only bananas were given to Bill.
the focus in S1 is on BILL. This means Sam didn’t give bananas to anyone else. S2 talks about giving apples to Mary, which doesn’t affect the claim about who got bananas. So, they are independent.
the focus in S1 is on SUE. This means Sam didn’t give apples to anyone else. S2 says that Tom also got apples. This directly contradicts S1.
the focus in S1 is on GRAPES. This means that Bill only got grapes and nothing else (no oranges). S2 says Bill didn’t get oranges, which aligns with this. So it’s entailed.
the focus in S1 is on APPLES. This means Bill got no other fruits, like bananas. S2 says Bill didn’t get bananas, which is entailed by S1.
the focus in S1 is on APPLES. This means Sue didn’t get bananas or any other fruit. S2 says Sue didn’t get bananas. This is directly entailed by S1.
the focus in S1 is on ELLEN. This means Ellen was the only recipient of oranges. S2 says Tom didn’t get oranges. That’s not a contradiction, nor does it follow directly—it’s independent.
the focus in S1 is on TOM. This means Tom was the only one who got apples. S2 says Mary didn’t get apples. This follows directly from S1, so it’s entailed.
the focus in S1 is on TOM. This means Tom was the only recipient of apples. S2 says Bill also got apples, which contradicts S1.
the focus in S1 is on SUE. This means Sue was the only one who got bananas. S2 says Tom didn’t get bananas. That matches the meaning of S1, so it’s entailed.
